<taxonomicName id="F429E04FF77B095B73ED5EDCA11E705D" LSID="A8070910-1C88-544C-80A0-AB63D52D87E7" authority="Erwin, 1970" authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1970" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Neoleistus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neoleistus">Neoleistus Erwin, 1970</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D88501B0176AB2C9A4B6804E2E4D0811" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="6E006EBB96339F9E0E3AB8D76644200A" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
<taxonomicName id="A97E2028DA2A447976007357C7678311" authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Neoleistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Neoleistus</taxonomicName>
Erwin, 1970b: 112. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="EB39D289FCFDF45ED6D5E27B5E5FB0B3" authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1843" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Leistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginosus">
<emphasis id="ABA7957EDBD7DED6BE2093EAC7F28047" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Leistus ferruginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mannerheim, 1843 by original designation. Etymology. From the Greek prefix 
<emphasis id="6112CA6A246D0E969B9680D6501A038A" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">neo</emphasis>
- (new) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="D0E61A44493B4DCBE2647D128AA4D6B5" authorityName="Froelich" authorityYear="1799" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Leistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="037BA433F092B48B377F5F7B3FEAB072" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Leistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="BE9655076759EB46E0178FB2731EB5A8" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">q.v</emphasis>
.], probably alluding to the fact that these 
<taxonomicName id="9ED90D9B1C3F9450E11AD4AD33FE7ED9" authorityName="Froelich" authorityYear="1799" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Leistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3BDB68C3BFC52BF18BB6B26B9872F7B9" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Leistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species inhabit the New World [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BC0C3FFE9437B92866ADF48326C07E4D" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="1DFB371605128F0E92439FC76FED730D" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CEC885FD1FFF099FC3C0D3BC40EAB936" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Three western North American species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="69954BC2218AF677B8A615B185071248" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="identification">
<paragraph id="35E80D8DCD82A953EBD48A9F5D986D22" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6391355C57EB9FE0AD10E6ECC55CA609" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Erwin (1970b) revised the species and provided a key for their identification.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="19A7374179F8BD25DC254AB14845C218" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="EFAD0E07105D1D971BAF823E7F0C5EEC" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="93FF17A8466DCE39FFE7ADBDC834AC7B" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
Perrault (1991a) added three species from the Far East (
<taxonomicName id="0E8ED7B8E8E57CBAE0B4509825C5DEA2" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1886" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Leistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulicollis">
<emphasis id="D6F759047FD5E25535F706178A504C4E" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Leistus angulicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fairmaire, 
<taxonomicName id="1BF9446BCEA296E106BADC50EF2E9006" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Leistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="CA510811D3B362846FCE95E89E58DB18" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Leistus niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gebler, and 
<taxonomicName id="B5D5C292A094516081AC02D49D96A700" authorityName="Perrault" authorityYear="1991" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Leistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shenseensis">
<emphasis id="4CF9E284AEF650552101F871EE21C88E" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Leistus shenseensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Perrault) to this subgenus but Shilenkov (1999: 76) rejected this association and the Asian species are listed in the nominotypical subgenus by 
<normalizedToken id="324EDC37D4E742087BB87D086123C104" originalValue="Farkač">Farkac</normalizedToken>
and Janata (2003: 81-82).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
